 {{t|uk|конто́ра|f}}, {{t+|uk|бюро́|n}}, {{t|uk|канцеля́рія|f}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|دَفْتَر|m}}, {{t+|ur|آفِس|m}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|ئىدارە}}, {{t|ug|ئىشخانا}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|idora}}, {{t+|uz|kontora}}, {{t+|uz|byuro}}, {{t+|uz|daftar}}, {{t+|uz|ofis}}, {{t+|uz|mahkama}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|văn phòng}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|bür}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|swyddfa|f}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|ביוראָ|n}}, {{t|yi|אָפֿיס|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|major governmental division}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|zyrë|f}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|գերատեսչություն}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|bulego}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|бюро|n}}, {{t+|bg|ведомство|n}}, {{t+|bg|министерство|n}}, {{t+|bg|управление|n}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|部}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|úřad|m}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|bureau|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bureau|n}}, {{t+|nl|dienst|m}}, {{t+|nl|overheidsdienst|m}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|skrivstova|f}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|virasto}}, {{t+|fi|ministeriö}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|bureau|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Amt|n}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|γραφείο|n}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מִשְׂרָד|m|tr=misrád}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|hivatal }}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|oifig|f}}\n* Kazakh: {{t|kk|ведомство}}, {{t|kk|министрлік}}\n* Khmer: {{t+|km|ការិយាល័យ}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|관청(官廳)}}, {{t+|ko|국(局)}}, {{t+|ko|청(廳)}}, {{t+|ko|부(部)}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|ministrija|f}}, {{t|lv|pārvalde|f}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|управа|f}}, {{t|mk|дирекција|f}}, {{t|mk|уред|m}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|tari}}\n* Middle English: {{t|enm|office}}\n* Mòcheno: {{t|mhn|omt|n}}\n* Persian:\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t|fa-ira|اِدارِه}}\n* Plautdietsch: {{t|pdt|Aumt|n}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|urząd|m}}, {{t+|pl|biuro|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|escritório|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|minister|n}}, {{t+|ro|departament|n}}, {{t+|ro|oficiu|n}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|ве́домство|n}}, {{t+|ru|министе́рство|n}}, {{t+|ru|управле́ние|n}}, {{t+|ru|бюро́|n}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|oifis|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|у́ред|m}}, {{t|sh|бѝро̄|m}}, {{t|sh|у̏права|f}}, {{t|sh|управитѐљство|n}}\n*: Latin: {{t+|sh|úred|m}}, {{t+|sh|bìrō|m}}, {{t+|sh|ȕprava|f}}, {{t+|sh|upravitèljstvo|n}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|úrad|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t|sl|urad|m}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|oficina|f}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|ofisi}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|byrå|c}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|tanggapan}}\n* Tajik: {{t+|tg|идора}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|اِدارَہ|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|kindness|good offices}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# To provide (someone) with an [[#Noun|office]].\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1966|author=United States. Congress. Senate|title=Hearings - Volume 8|isbn=|page=451|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1HCrwgYccLQC&\n|passage=Is he '''officed''' in Congressional Relations or is he '''officed''' in SCA?}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1976|author=|title=General Technical Report RM.|isbn=|page=128|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=EAzxAAAAMAAJ&\n|passage=Prior to that time, Station personnel were first '''officed''' in temporary wartime barracks on the campus and then on the second floor of the Journalism Building.}}\n# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To have an [[#Noun|office]].\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=December 2, 1988|author=Grant Pick|title=He Survived Operation Greylord|work=Chicago Reader|url=http://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/he-survived-operation-greylord/Content?oid=873095|passage=\"I believed that Dave was just doing a favor for his brother,\" said Somerville, who added that he assumed Lou and Dave '''officed''' together.|accessdate=1 July 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101203133823/http://www.chicagoreader.com/chicago/he-survived-operation-greylord/Content?oid=873095|archivedate=3 December 2010}}\n\n===References===\n<references/>\n* ''Webster's New Collegiate Dictionary'', 7th ed. \"office\". G. & C. Merriam Co. ([[w:Springfield, Massachusetts|Springfield]]), 1967.\n* ''The Century Dictionary''. \"[https://web.archive.org/web/20231102053111/http://triggs.djvu.org/century-dictionary.com/nph-chw.php?query=office&type=dicts office]\". The Century Co. (New York), 1911.\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=ceffio|coiffe}}\n\n{{C|en|Collectives|Rooms|Toilet (room)}}\n\n==French==\n\n===Etymology===\n{{ety|fr|:bor|la:officium}}\n{{bor+|fr|la|officium}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{fr-IPA}}\n* {{audio|fr|Fr-office.ogg}}\n* {{audio|fr|LL-Q150 (fra)-Jérémy-Günther-Heinz Jähnick-office.wav|a=<<France>> (<<Somain>>)}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|m}}\n\n# charge, [[task]], [[mandate]]\n# administrative bureau, [[department]]\n# religious service, notably liturgical office.                                                                                                                          1886, Cora Pearl, ''Mémoires,'' ch 3''.  \"''Ce qu'il en coute d'aller seule à l'office.\"  \"What it costs to go alone to church.\"\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|fr|couteau d'office}}\n* {{l|fr|faire office de}}\n* {{l|fr|office des Grandes Heures}}\n* {{l|fr|office de tourisme}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{fr-noun|f}}\n\n# [[pantry]], room [[adjoining]] a [[kitchen]] where dishes, [[table linens]], and [[provisions]] are kept\n#: {{ux|fr|Il avait trouvé dans l''''office''' un saucisson, des boîtes de sardines, du fromage de Hollande.|He had found in the '''pantry''' a sausage, some tins of sardines, and some Dutch cheese}}\n# place where a [[household]]'s table (food and drink)-related services are conducted, especially by domestic staff\n\n===References===\n* {{R:NPLarousse}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{R:fr:TLFi}}\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{l|fr|coiffe}}, {{l|fr|coiffé}}\n\n==Latin==\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|la|verb form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|officiō||2|s|pres|actv|impr}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|la|noun form}}\n\n# {{inflection of|la|offex||abl|s}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Etymology 1===\nFrom {{bor|enm|fro|office}}, from {{der|enm|la|officium}}, contracted form of {{m|la|opificium}}.\n\n====Alternative forms====\n* {{alter|enm|offiz|offis|offyce|ofys|offise|ofice|offece|offys}}\n\n====Pronunciation====\n* {{IPA|enm|/ɔˈfiːs(ə)/|/ˈɔfis(ə)/}}\n\n====Noun====\n{{enm-noun|offices}}\n\n# The state of being [[employed]] or having a work or job; [[employment]]:\n## [[ecclesiastical|Ecclesiastical]] or [[religious]] work; a church [[career]].\n## {{lb|enm|rare}} [[unskilled|Unskilled]] work; any work that is unimportant or base.\n# A [[position]] of [[responsibility]] or [[control]]; a crucial occupation:\n#* {{c.|1300}}, ''St. Thomas Becket'', ll. 244 ff.\n#*: {{quote|enm|[[þis|Þis]] [[holi]] [[man|Man]] was i-torned...<br>To a [[gret]] [[office]] of [[the|þe]] world.}}\n## A [[clerical]] or [[church]] post or position; a [[religious]] {{l|en|office}}.\n## A governmental or administrative position or post; a [[political]] {{l|en|office}}.\n##* {{c.|1300}}, ''St. Thomas Becket'', ll. 223 ff.\n##*: {{quote|enm|He [[came|cam]] to court and was in [[good|guod]] [[office|offiz]]<br>With [[the|þe]] [[erchebischop]] of [[Kaunterburi]].}}\n## The [[situation]], [[status]], or [[rank]] one has in the wider [[world]] or within [[society]].\n# A task, [[chore]] or [[assignment]], especially one which is  [[important]] or [[required]]; an [[obligation]]:\n#* {{quote-text|enm|year=c. 1330|title=Lai le Freine\n|passage=[[þe|Þe]] porter of [[þe]] [[abbay]]... [[did|dede]] his [[office|ofice]] in [[þe]] clos.}}\n## The [[role]], [[purpose]], or [[intended]] use or utility of something (especially a bodily part).\n##* {{quote-text|enm|year=c. 1380|translator=w:Geoffrey Chaucer|author=w:Boethius|title=[[w:Boece (Chaucer)|Boece]]\n|passage=[[sche|Sche]] say me... withouten [[office]] of [[tunge]] and [[al]] [[dumb|dowmb]].}}\n##* {{c.|1390}}, [[w:John Gower|John Gower]], ''[[w:Confessio Amantis|Confessio Amantis]]'', Book VII, ll. 467 ff.:\n##*: {{quote|enm|As it is in [[physic|Phisique]] write<br>Of livere, of lunge, of galle, of splen,<br>[[thei|Thei]] [[all]]e unto the [[herte]] ben Servantz, and ech in his [[office]]<br>[[intends|Entendeth]] to [[do]]n him service.}}\n##* {{c.|1395}}, [[w:Geoffrey Chaucer|Geoffrey Chaucer]], \"[[w:The_Wife_of_Bath%27s_Tale|The Tale of the Wyf of Bathe]]\" in ''[[w:The Canterbury Tales|Tales of Caunterbury]]'', ll. 127 ff.:\n##*: {{quote|enm|[[membres|Membres]] of [[generacioun]]... maked been for [[both]]e;<br>That is to seye, for [[office]] and for [[ese]]<br>Of engendrure.}}\n## A [[task]] or [[function]] that one organ does to assist another or the body as a whole.\n##* {{quote-text|enm|year=1340|title=Ayenbite\n|passage=[[þe|Þe]] [[mouþ]] heþ [[tuo]] [[office]]s, huer-of [[þe]] [[on]] [[belongeþ]] to [[þe]] zuelȝ...<br>[[þe|Þe]] oþer [[zuo]] is in [[speche]].}}\n## A religious [[ceremony]] or [[ritual]]; a task performed for religious reasons.\n##* {{ante|1300}}, ''Arthour & Merlin'', ll. 2758 ff.:\n##*: {{quote|enm|[[þe|Þe]] holy [[bishop|bischop]]...<br>For him [[dede]] [[þe]] [[office]];<br>In [[erþe]] he was sikerliche<br>[[layd|Layd]] swiþe nobeliche.}}\n## {{lb|enm|Christianity}} The beginning or the initial portion of the [[Eucharist]].\n##* {{c.|1300}}, ''St. Thomas Becket'', ll. 942 ff.:\n##*: {{quote|enm|He song þulke [[mass]]e ilome, for al-so heo bi-ginnez<br>Þe furste [[office|offiz]] is [[propre]] inov to þe stat [[þat]] he was [[inne|Inne]].}}\n## A core human [[faculty]] {{gloss|e.g. [[movement]], [[talking]], [[literacy]]}}\n# A part, [[faculty]], or [[division]] of a [[larger]] body:\n## A [[part]] of a [[house]] or [[estate]] devoted to manual work and [[storage]].\n##* {{ante|1422}}, petition, P.R.O. 117, 5842:\n##*: {{quote|enm|... [[abbeyes|Abbeyes]], Priories, hospitals, [[chaunteries]] and chappels, [[chace]]s, parkes, [[office]]s, milnes, weres...}}\n## A [[part]] or [[subdivision]] of an [[estate]] devoted to a specified function.\n## {{lb|enm|rare}} A [[part]] or [[subdivision]] of a [[government]] devoted to a specified function.\n##* '''1435''', petition, P.R.O. 130, 6460A:\n##*: {{quote|enm|John [[duc|Duc]] of Bedford... Admirall of England in the [[office]] of [[þe]] admiralte in the Countees of Kent, Sussex...}}\n# An [[inquest]] undertaken to investigate the [[possession]] of land or property.\n#* '''1432''', petition, P.R.O. 26, 1259:\n#*: {{quote|enm|Of the [[which]]e [[maner|Maner]] the [[seyd]] Oratrice... be an [[office|Offyce]] was put out.}}\n# The intended or [[ideal]] working or [[operation]] of something.\n# An [[officeholder]] invested with powers and authority.\n#* {{quote-book|enm|year=c. 1440|translator=Stephen Scrope|author=Christine de Pisan|title=The Epistle of Othea|page=85\n|passage=He pleide so sweetly [[þat]]... [[alle]] [[þe]] [[helly]] [[offices]] [[left]]e there besinesses.}}\n# {{lb|enm|rare}} A [[building]] or [[structure]] used for [[business]] purposes; an office.\n#* {{quote-text|enm|year=c. 1395|author=w:Geoffrey Chaucer|chapter=[[w:The Friar's Tale|The Freres Tale]]|title=[[w:Canterbury Tales|Tales of Caunterbury]]\n|passage=...I wol han .xij. pens, though that she be [[wood]],<br>Or I wol sompne [[hir]] vn to our [[office]]...}}\n#* {{quote-text|enm|year=1440|title=Promptorium Parvulorum|page=363\n|passage=[[office|Offyce]], or place of [[office|offyce]], ''{{l|la|officina}}''.}}\n# {{lb|enm|rare}} The [[process]] or [[undertaking]] of a task or assignment.\n#* {{c.|1300}}, ''The Romance of Sir Beues of Hamtoun'', ll. 3555 ff.:\n#*: {{quote|enm|While Beues was in þat [[office]],<br>[[þe|Þe]] kinges sone...<br>A ȝede to Beves stable.}}\n# {{lb|enm|rare}} The [[activities]] typical of and concomitant to one's place in society.\n# {{lb|enm|rare}} A favour; a [[beneficial]] deed or act.\n#* {{RQ:Wycliffe NT Lichfield|2 Corinthians|9|12|70|v|column=2|foꝛ þe mynyſterie of þis '''office'''. not oneli filliþ þoo þingis þat failen to hooli men .· but alſo multeplieþ many þankyngis to god|translation=As the administering of this favour doesn't just supply the things that holy men are lacking, but also overflows in many thanks to God.}}\n\n=====Related terms=====\n* {{l|enm|officen}}\n* {{l|enm|officer}}\n* {{l|enm|official}}\n\n=====Descendants=====\n* {{desc|en|office}}\n* {{desc|sco|office|offish}}\n\n=====References=====\n* {{R:MED Online|entry=offī̆ce|part of speech=n|id= MED30297 |accessdate=2019-03-17}}\n\n===Etymology 2===\nFrom {{bor|enm|fro|officier}}.\n\n====Verb====\n{{head|enm|verb|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|officen}}\n\n{{C|enm|Buildings and structures|Communication|Household|Occupations|Offices|People|Physiology|Property law|Religion|Society}}\n\n==Norman==\n\n===Noun===\n{{nrf-noun|m}}\n\n# {{lb|nrf|Jersey}} {{l|en|office}}\n#* {{quote-book|nrf|year=2010|location=w:Jersey|publisher=Le Don Balleine, L'Office du Jèrriais|title=Mêfie-té des Monstres: Tchiques légendes dé Jèrri|isbn=978-0-9566289-0-9|passage=L''''Office''' du Jèrriais|translation=The '''Office''' of Jèrriais}}\n\n==Old French==\n\n===Noun===\n{{fro-noun|m}}\n\n# {{l|en|office}} {{gloss|building; room}}\n# {{l|en|office}} {{gloss|position, role, job}}\n# [[service]]\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|fr|office}}\n\n===References===\n* {{R:Anglo-Norman On-Line Hub}}"}}